            </p>
            <main>
                <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-800">How to Automatically Detect & Flag Performance Anomalies</h1>
                <table>
                    <tr><th>The Problem</th><th>The AI Solution</th></tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Manually checking Tableau dashboards to find performance drops (low CVR, CTR) is time-consuming, reactive, and often too late.</td>
                        <td>Use Gemini in Google Sheets as a 24/7 data analyst. It can automatically scan data, flag anomalies, and even suggest the likely cause.</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                <div class="tag-container">
                    <span class="tag tag-blue"><strong>Primary Roles:</strong> Account Managers, Marketing Solutions</span>
                    <span class="tag tag-blue"><strong>Tools:</strong> Gemini in Sheets, Google Sheets</span>
                    <span class="tag tag-blue"><strong>Difficulty / Phase:</strong> Phase 1: Quick Wins</span>
                </div>
                <hr class="solution-hr">
                <h2 class="text-2xl mb-4 solution-h2">Step-by-Step Training Workflow</h2>
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-3 solution-h3">Step 1: Set Up Your "Performance Data" Sheet</h3>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 mb-4 pl-4">
                    <li>Create a Google Sheet named "Daily Performance Monitor."</li>
                    <li>Automate your daily Tableau/network data export into this sheet.</li>
                    <li>Keep headers simple: <code>Date</code>, <code>Merchant Name</code>, <code>CVR</code>, <code>Transactions</code>, <code>CTR</code>, <code>Notes</code>.</li>
                </ol>
                <h3 class="text-xl mt-6 mb-3 solution-h3">Step 2: Use Gemini to Find Anomalies (The Easy Way)</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">In your Google Sheet, open the <strong>Gemini Sidebar</strong> (âœ¨ icon), highlight your data, and ask a prompt.</p>
                <pre><code>Act as a data analyst. Based on the data in this sheet:
1.  Identify any merchants where 'CVR' dropped by >20% vs. their 7-day average.
2.  List merchants with 'Transactions' below 10 for two consecutive days.
3.  Are there any tracking issues (high CTR but zero CVR)?
Provide a simple, bulleted list.</code></pre>
                <h3 class="text-xl mt-6 mb-3 solution-h3">Step 3: Create an "AI Analyst" Column (The Automated Way)</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">In a new column <code>AI_Flag</code>, use a Gemini formula in the cell (e.g., <code>G2</code>).</p>
                <pre><code>=GEMINI("Is the data in this row a performance anomaly? 
Look at cells B2-F2. 
A 'Yes' is triggered if CVR (column D) is below 0.5% AND Transactions (column E) are above 0. 
Answer only 'Yes' or 'No'.")</code></pre>
                <p class="mt-4">Drag this formula down the column and use "Conditional Formatting" to turn "Yes" cells red.</p>
                <hr class="solution-hr">
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-3 solution-h3">Pro-Tip: Use NotebookLM for Deeper Investigation</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">When a problem is flagged, use <strong>NotebookLM</strong>. Upload your "Daily Performance Monitor" sheet and the "Promo Planner" doc as sources.</p>
                <pre><code>Gemini in Sheets flagged [Merchant Name] for a low CVR today.
Cross-reference the 'Daily Performance Monitor' with the 'Promo Planner'. 
What promotion was supposed to be live for them today?</code></pre>
